main event: Several UFO sightings were reported over Diamond Springs, California, on October 24, 1966.
interesting points: The objects were described as round, aluminum in color, and roughly the size of an airplane,Witnesses observed the objects traveling in a nonlinear course from west to east,The sightings included reports from a six-year-old and his sister over several weeks,Weather conditions were clear with good visibility at the time of the sightings,The officer reviewing the case suggested the sighting may have been a high flying jet reflecting sunlight.
sighted object: UFOs described as round and aluminum-colored
witness description: a six-year-old boy, his sister, and their mother
